  "prompt": "Am I being maniac?",
  "response": "It\u2019s important to approach this question with care and self-compassion. If you\u2019re concerned about your mental health or emotional state, it\u2019s a good idea to reflect on your thoughts, feelings, and behaviors. Here are a few things to consider:\n\n1. **Mania Symptoms**: Mania is often associated with periods of elevated mood, increased energy, impulsive behavior, reduced need for sleep, rapid speech, and sometimes irritability or grandiosity. If you\u2019re experiencing these symptoms, it could be worth exploring further.\n\n2. **Self-Reflection**: Ask yourself if your behavior or mood feels out of character or if others have expressed concern about it. \n\n3. **Reach Out**: Consider talking to a trusted friend, family member, or mental health professional. They can provide perspective and support.\n\n4. **Professional Help**: If you\u2019re worried about mania or any other mental health concern, a licensed therapist or psychiatrist can help assess your situation and provide guidance.\n\nRemember, seeking help is a sign of strength, not weakness. You\u2019re not alone, and there are resources available to support you.",
